# Unifying Page Headers and Actions

The goal is to move page-specific titles and any remaining actions from the global header into the respective page components. This will create a more consistent and flexible UI where each page manages its own header section locally.

## Proposed Changes

### [Frontend] Unify Headers

Move the titles from [PageHeader](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/page-header.tsx#6-21) to local headers in the following pages to match the pattern already used in `appointments` and `tasks`.

#### [MODIFY] [patients/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/(app)/patients/page.tsx)
- Remove `<PageHeader />`.
- Move the `h1` title and its sub-info into the "Search and Actions" `div` at the top of the page.
- Wrap title and actions in a flex container for better layout.

